    "pr_title": "fix(minimax): request hex TTS output explicitly",
    "pr_body": "## What Problem This Solves\nMiniMax TTS response handling decodes `data.audio` as hex, but the request on current main does not explicitly ask MiniMax for hex/non-streaming output. The artifact shows #73079 is the narrow contributor fix, but its Real behavior proof is failing.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nRepair the existing contributor branch instead of replacing it: it is MiniMax-only, maintainer_can_modify is true, has no hydrated review-comment blockers, and only touches `extensions/minimax/tts.ts` plus the focused speech-provider test.\n\n## User Impact\nMiniMax speech generation should stop depending on provider defaults for audio encoding/streaming shape.\n\n## Evidence\nSource PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/73079 by @efe-arv. Current main at d6111ff72c77ff16978ced1faa451546d9911e83 lacks explicit `output_format`/`stream` in `extensions/minimax/tts.ts`. Run `pnpm test extensions/minimax/speech-provider.test.ts` and `pnpm check:changed` after repair, then perform fresh Codex /review before any merge.",
